1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:05,145
Data science experts and data analysts often approach data wrangling is a flexible,

2
00:00:05,145 --> 00:00:08,265
multi-step process that offers various options.

3
00:00:08,265 --> 00:00:11,565
For example, depending on the use case and the data itself,

4
00:00:11,565 --> 00:00:14,280
some data wranglers choose to gather data from

5
00:00:14,280 --> 00:00:17,640
many sources and combine their data before moving on to

6
00:00:17,640 --> 00:00:20,505
the assessment and cleaning stages whereas

7
00:00:20,505 --> 00:00:24,165
others choose to combine data after the cleaning stage.

8
00:00:24,165 --> 00:00:27,780
There are a number of skills that you can learn to help you build this type of

9
00:00:27,780 --> 00:00:31,350
decision-making expertise when presented with these choices.

10
00:00:31,350 --> 00:00:36,360
Experts in this space also typically access different types of reliable data sources,

11
00:00:36,360 --> 00:00:38,860
i.e, data sources that can be trusted.

12
00:00:38,860 --> 00:00:42,755
Some examples of the sources used in industry include surveys,

13
00:00:42,755 --> 00:00:44,555
data provided by governments,

14
00:00:44,555 --> 00:00:46,265
data gathered by hospitals,

15
00:00:46,265 --> 00:00:50,940
marketing data, and data gathered by Internet of Things devices.

